  <!-- Who is Imam Ali -->
  <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto p-6 bg-gray-800 rounded-lg mb-10">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-green-300 mb-4">🧔 Who is Imam Ali?</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-200 mb-2">
      Imam Ali ibn Abi Talib (AS) was the cousin and son-in-law of Prophet Muhammad ﷺ, the first male to accept Islam, and the fourth caliph in Sunni tradition but the first Imam in Shia belief.
    </p>
    <p class="text-gray-300">
      He was born inside the Kaaba and is known for his bravery, justice, knowledge, and devotion to Islam. His famous title is <strong>Asadullah</strong> – "The Lion of Allah".
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- Life Story -->
  <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto p-6 bg-gray-800 rounded-lg mb-10">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-green-300 mb-4">📜 Key Moments in His Life</h2>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-300 space-y-2">
      <li>✅ Born in the Kaaba in Mecca</li>
      <li>✅ Slept in the Prophet's bed during the Hijrah to protect him</li>
      <li>✅ Married Fatimah (RA), daughter of Prophet Muhammad ﷺ</li>
      <li>✅ Fought in all major battles: Badr, Uhud, Khaybar</li>
      <li>✅ Known for his justice as Caliph (656–661 CE)</li>
      <li>✅ Martyred in Masjid Kufa in 661 CE by Ibn Muljam</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <!-- Sunni Hadith Section -->
  <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto p-6 bg-gray-800 rounded-lg mb-10">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-yellow-400 mb-4">📚 Sunni Hadith on Imam Ali’s Wilayah</h2>
    <div class="text-gray-200 space-y-4">
      <div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg text-white">📖 Hadith al-Ghadir</h3>
        <p>"Whoever I am his Mawla (master), Ali is his Mawla." – <em>Sahih Tirmidhi, Musnad Ahmad</em></p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg text-white">🌙 Hadith of the Gate of Knowledge</h3>
        <p>"I am the city of knowledge and Ali is its gate." – <em>Sunan al-Tirmidhi</em></p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg text-white">🛡️ Battle of Khaybar</h3>
        <p>"Tomorrow I shall give the banner to a man who loves Allah and His Messenger and Allah and His Messenger love him... Ali." – <em>Sahih Bukhari, Sahih Muslim</em></p>
      </div>
